“Is Monmouth to be there, too?”
“Oh, yes, Harry.”
“He bores me dreadfully, almost as much as he bores her. She is very clever, too
clever for a woman. She lacks the indefinable charm of weakness. It is the feet of clay
that make the gold of the image precious. Her feet are very pretty, but they are not feet
of clay. White porcelain feet, if you like. They have been through the fire, and what fire
does not destroy, it hardens. She has had experiences.”
“How long has she been married?” asked Dorian.
“An eternity, she tells me. I believe, according to the peerage, it is ten years, but ten
